---
title: Spinach Ravioli with Crispy Salami 3 Easy Steps to a Delicious Dinner
description: A few minutes in a hot pan is all it takes to transform diced salami into the crispy, punchy, and ultra-savory topping of your dreams. You’ll crisp up that salami and sprinkle it over rich, comforting spinach-ricotta ravioli tossed in a creamy garlic sauce with fresh tomato. A side of buttery toasted baguette completes the meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/673b99bcfd3e9058428acbe3-2a76a80e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/673b99bcfd3e9058428acbe3-en-US.pdf
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
nutrition:
  calories: 730 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 25 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1460 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spinach-ravioli-with-crispy-salami-673b99bcfd3e9058428acbe3
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce. Dice @Tomato{1}(diced into 1/4-inch pieces).

Heat a large dry #pot{} over high heat. Add @Diced Salami{2%ounce} and cook,
stirring occasionally, until slightly crispy, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat.
Transfer to a #paper towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pot.

In pot used for salami, whisk together @Cream Sauce Base{4%ounce},
@Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, and 3/4 cup water over high heat. Bring to a boil.

Once boiling, reduce heat to medium. Stir in tomato and @Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli{9%ounce};
cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until ravioli are al dente and sauce has
thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Meanwhile, cut @Demi-Baguette{1} in half lengthwise and toast until golden brown.
Spread with @Butter{1%TBSP}. Halve on a diagonal.

> Use 2 TBSP butter if making 4 servings.

Divide ravioli between shallow #bowls{}; top with crispy salami and
@Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} or as many as you like. Serve with buttery toast on
the side.